<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-11-12T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-11-12T10:00:00-05:00" n="456" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d456">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/6661:
                                    Telegram</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss>
                                    </hi>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-11-12T17:00:00+02:00">November 12, 1940—5 p.m.</date>
                                        <lb/> [Received November 14—9:32 a.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>299. Department’s telegram No. 248, November 7, 6 p.m. In reply
                                    to my formal inquiry the Under Secretary of State for Foreign
                                    Affairs informs me by his note No. 33953 dated November 11,
                                    1940, that “a state of war exists in Greece since October 28th
                                    of this year at 5:30 a.m. at which time Italy launched an
                                    unexpected attack against Greece”.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacVeagh</hi>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>